title: Summer Wish
description: When Craig decides to keep a lightning bug in a jar, he disrupts the delicate balance of Summer.

title: Hyde & Zeke
description: Craig and his friends are challenged to find the greatest hider that Hide and Seek has ever known.

title: Locked Out Cold
description: On the eve of a big holiday party, the Williams kids are locked out of the house, leading to a frantic search all over town for a spare key.

title: Silver Fist Returns
description: There's a thief in the Creek, and there is only one hero who can stop them: SILVER FIST!

title: Turning the Tables
description: Craig dines at the restaurant where his older brother works and orders up a plate of REVENGE... and lots of breadsticks.

title: Craig and the Kid's Table
description: It's a Williams Family Thanksgiving, which means it's time to reunite The Kid's Table! But when Bernard accidentally destroys dessert, Craig uses the power of the Kids Table to help save his brother from certain grounding.

title: The Haunted Dollhouse
description: Craig and his friends find themselves being followed by a creepy doll and its haunted dollhouse.

title: The Anniversary Box
description: Craig is entrusted with a special anniversary gift for his mom, and immediately loses it in the Creek.

title: Beyond the Overpass
description: The Capture the Flag war is over. Craig returns to the Creek, hoping to get some recognition for his heroic deeds, but finds a new quest instead.

title: My Stare Lady
description: Craig enters a dangerous staring contest, hoping to win another one of Kenneth's Cubes.

title: Doorway to Helen
description: Craig makes a long distance connection with a kid that loves the creek as much as he does.

title: Creek Talent Extravaganza
description: Hoping to help the Creek Daycare, Craig organizes a talent show.

title: Scoutguest
description: Craig finds himself with an unlikely house guest when Jason the Junior Forest Scout sleeps over.

title: Puppy Love
description: Wildernessa's beloved dog goes missing, so Craig joins the search to track him down.

title: Better Than You
description: The Squashinator challenges Craig to a battle he can't refuse.

title: Bored Games
description: Bored on a rainy day, Craig, Kelsey and JP put together their broken board games and find themselves transported into the ultimate gaming challenge.

title: The Dream Team
description: Craig and his cousin, Bryson, join forces for an action packed weekend at their grandparents house.

title: Return of the Honeysuckle Rangers
description: Craig discovers that the Honeysuckle Rangers have snuck into his side of the Creek to steal his most prized possession.

title: The Other Side
description: Craig, Kelsey and JP must journey past the Overpass into uncharted territory, the Other Side of the Creek.

title: The Champion's Hike
description: Craig joins his former enemies, the Champions of the Other Side of the Creek, on a hike to a secret waterfall.

title: Breaking the Ice
description: While searching a once unreachable part of the Creek, Craig gets stranded with his longtime rival, Wildernessa!

title: Kelsey the Author
description: Craig and Stacks help Kelsey become a real author turning her story into a book!

title: Lost & Found
description: Craig and his friends visit the Creek's Lost & Found, hoping to claim a puzzle cube.

title: Fire & Ice
description: Kelsey and Stacks write a story for book club, which turns out to be more personal than Kelsey realized.

title: Memories of Bobby
description: When a pillar of the Creek community leaves, our trio mourns their loss by remembering the good times.

title: Dodgy Decisions
description: Friends and rivals are pitted against each other in a dangerous game of dodgeball.

title: Opposite Day
description: Opposite Day turns out to be the opposite of what nobody didn't think it wouldn't be.

title: In Search of Lore
description: Craig searches for more clues to aid his quest for the Heart of the Forest.

title: Galactic Goodbyes
description: Craig and Sparkle Cadet put together a band to sing a goodbye to a long lost friend.

title: Fort Williams
description: When Craig can't go to the Creek, he and his mom decide to build the biggest blanket fort in the world!

title: Sink or Swim Team
description: Craig offers to help the Sewer Queen by going undercover as a member of the swim team.

title: The Chef's Challenge
description: Craig and his friends find themselves entering a cooking battle for a piece of the cube.

title: Back to Cool
description: Craig goes to extreme lengths to keep up with the fall fashion trends.

title: The Quick Name
description: Craig tries to rid himself of a bad nickname.

title: Adventures in Baby Casino
description: Craig goes all in at the Baby Casino.

title: Kelsey the Elder
description: A spat between the Elders of the Creek leaves an opening in their tabletop role playing game, so Kelsey joins the campaign!

title: Craig of the Street
description: Craig visits his cousin, Bryson, and they go on a quest through the streets of New Jersey.

title: Grandma Smugglers
description: Craig helps Raj sneak his grandmother away to the Creek.

title: Sour Candy Trials
description: Craig goes on a mind-bending journey as he tries to eat the most sour candy in the Creek!

title: Jacob of the Creek
description: A terrible haircut forces Craig to go undercover at the Creek.

title: The Sparkle Solution
description: When Craig is having trouble with some math homework, Sparkle Cadet comes to the rescue.

title: Chrono Moss
description: Craig and his friends come upon a mysterious Moss Village, which could aid them in their quest for the Heart of the Forest.

title: Craig to the Future
description: The Witches of the Creek use their mystical powers to give Craig and his friends a glimpse into the future.

title: The Legend of the Library
description: When the library is thrown into disarray, an ancient ghost is awoken.

title: The Evolution of Craig
description: Craig rescues a tadpole and decides to raise him into a level 100 frog!
